]]<br>[[Los Angeles FC]]{{#tag:ref|[[Chivas USA|Club Deportivo Chivas USA]] was a Major League Soccer club that existed between 2005 and 2014 before folding.<ref name=\"LAFC\">{{cite press release|title=MLS announces new strategy for Los Angeles market, 2015 conference alignment|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2014/10/27/mls-announces-new-strategy-los-angeles-market|publisher=Major League Soccer|date=October 27, 2014|accessdate=October 27, 2014}}</ref>|group=note}}}}\n| align=center|{{sort|0|\u2014}}\n|-\n| [[Chicago metropolitan area|Chicago]]\n| United States\n| 3\n| 9,512,999\n| 5\n| {{sort|1|[[Chicago Bears|Bears]]}}{{#tag:ref|The [[History of the Chicago Cardinals|Chicago Cardinals]] were a charter franchise of the NFL, before moving to St. Louis in 1960.|group=note}}\n| {{sort|2|[[Chicago Cubs|Cubs]]<br>[[Chicago White Sox|White Sox]]}}\n| {{sort|1|[[Chicago Bulls|Bulls]]}}{{#tag:ref|Chicago has had two prior NBA teams: the [[Chicago Stags|Stags]] existed from 1946 to 1950 before folding, and the [[Chicago Packers|Packers]]/[[Chicago Zephyrs|Zephyrs]] played from 1961 to 1963, before moving to Baltimore.|group=note}}\n| {{sort|1|[[Chicago Blackhawks|Blackhawks]]}}\n| 6\n| {{sort|1|[[Chicago Fire FC|Fire]]}}\n| align=center|{{sort|0|\u2014}}\n|-\n| [[San Francisco Bay Area]]\n| United States\n| 6\n| 6,657,982\n| 5\n| {{sort|1|[[San Francisco 49ers|49ers]]}}{{#tag:ref|The [[History of the Oakland Raiders|Oakland Raiders]] called Oakland home from 1960 until 1982 and again from 1995 until 2019 before [[Oakland Raiders relocation to Las Vegas|relocating to Las Vegas]] becoming the [[Las Vegas Raiders]].|group=note}}\n| {{sort|2|[[San Francisco Giants|Giants]]<br>[[Oakland Athletics|Athletics]]}}\n| {{sort|1|[[Golden State Warriors|Warriors]]}}\n| {{sort|1|[[San Jose Sharks|Sharks]]}}{{#tag:ref|The [[California Golden Seals]] were an NHL expansion team which played in Oakland from [[1967\u201368 NHL season|1967]]\u2013[[1975\u201376 NHL season|76]], when 